The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry and optimization, specifically the Maximum Scatter TSP problem. This problem involves finding a tour that visits every point exactly once, maximizing the length of the shortest edge in the tour. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry and approximation algorithms to provide a solution for this problem in doubling metrics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which could also place it in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
